e if a massive star or a white dwarf binary ejected from either\ngalaxy could be the supernova progenitor. Finally, we consider several other\nhypotheses for the nature of the object, including the jets of an active\ngalactic nucleus (AGN) or the remnant of a nearby stellar super-flare.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 25 Jan 2022 00:51:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-16"}
{"id":"2201.10027","submitter":"Saikumar Reddy Yeddula Mr","authors":"Saikumar R. Yeddula, Juan Guzm\\'an-I\\~nigo, Aimee S. Morgans","title":"A solution for the quasi-one-dimensional linearised Euler equations with\n  heat transfer","comments":"15 Pages, 6 figures. Will be published soon in JFM Rapids","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1017/jfm.2022.101","report-no":null,"categories":"physics.flu-dyn math.AP","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0/","abstract":"  The unsteady response of nozzles with steady heat transfer forced by acoustic\nand/or entropy waves is modelled. The approach is based on the\nquasi-one-dimensional linearised Euler equations. The equations are cast in\nterms of three variables, namely the dimensionless mass, stagnation temperature\nand entropy fluctuations, which are invariants of the system at zero frequency\nand with no heat transfer. The resulting first-order system of differential\nequations is then solved using the Magnus expansion method, where the\nperturbation parameters are the normalised frequency and the volumetric heat\ntransfer. In this work, a measure of the flow non-isentropicity (in this case\nthe steady heat transfer) is used for the first time as an expansion parameter.\nThe solution method was applied to a converging-diverging nozzle with constant\nheat transfer for both sub-critical and super-critical flow cases, showing good\nagreement with numerical predictions. It was observed that the acoustic and\nentropy transfer functions of the nozzle strongly depend on the frequency and\nheat transfer.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 25 Jan 2022 01:04:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-02"}
