ing effects into\nconsideration, we show that smaller scale, more frequent structures with PVI\nbetween, $1\\lesssim PVI \\lesssim 6$, play the major role in magnetic energy\ndissipation. The number density of such events is strongly associated with the\nglobal solar wind temperature, with denser intervals being associated with\nhigher $T_{p}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 25 Jan 2022 03:05:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 26 Jan 2022 03:14:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-14"}
